Enum WMIAuthenticationLevel

All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<WMIAuthenticationLevel>
public enum WMIAuthenticationLevel
extends java.lang.Enum<WMIAuthenticationLevel>

Authentication levels that can be provided to WMI connections. The official documentation for WMI authentication levels can be found on the MSDN.

Since:
5.5.5.4

Enum Constant Summary
CALL
          Authenticates only at the beginning of each remote procedure call when the server receives the request.
CONNECT
          Authenticates the credentials of the client only when the client establishes a relationship with the server.
DEFAULT
          The default authentication level.
NONE
          No authentication
PACKET
          Authenticates that all data received is from the expected client.
PACKET_INTEGRITY
          Authenticates and verifies that none of the data transferred between client and server has been modified.
PACKET_PRIVACY
          Authenticates all previous levels and encrypts the argument value of each remote procedure call.

Enum Constant Detail

CALL

public static final WMIAuthenticationLevel CALL
Authenticates only at the beginning of each remote procedure call when the server receives the request. Datagram transports use RPC_C_AUTHN_LEVEL_PKT instead.

CONNECT

public static final WMIAuthenticationLevel CONNECT
Authenticates the credentials of the client only when the client establishes a relationship with the server. Datagram transports always use RPC_AUTHN_LEVEL_PKT instead.

DEFAULT

public static final WMIAuthenticationLevel DEFAULT
The default authentication level. This is the level that is used for any WMI connections that do not accept an authentication level.

NONE

public static final WMIAuthenticationLevel NONE
No authentication

PACKET

public static final WMIAuthenticationLevel PACKET
Authenticates that all data received is from the expected client.

PACKET_INTEGRITY

public static final WMIAuthenticationLevel PACKET_INTEGRITY
Authenticates and verifies that none of the data transferred between client and server has been modified.

PACKET_PRIVACY

public static final WMIAuthenticationLevel PACKET_PRIVACY
Authenticates all previous levels and encrypts the argument value of each remote procedure call.
